AB  - Components of previous computer security systems were designed independently from one another and often were difficult to integrate. The IBM Transaction Security System was designed to meet the requirements of the financial industry. It implements the Common Cryptographic Architecture and includes a comprehensive set of security products that allow users to implement end-to-end secure systems with IBM components. The system includes: 1. a mainframe host-attached Network Security Processor, 2. high-performance encryption adapters for the IBM PC and PS/2 Micro Channel, 3. an RS-232 attached Security Interface Unit, and 4. a credit-card-size state-of-the-art Personal Security card containing a high-performance microprocessor. The application programming interface provides common programming in the host and the workstation. It also supports all Systems Application Architecture languages except REXX and RPG. Applications may be written to run on MVS and PC DOS operating systems.
